text: Cletus Maanu Paul (18 November 1938 – 15 September 2022) was a New Zealand Māori leader. He was co-chair of the New Zealand Maori Council. In 2013, Paul was diagnosed with cancer. He died on 15 September 2022, at the age of 83. ==References== Category:1930s births Category:Year of birth missing Category:2022 deaths Category:New Zealand educators Category:New Zealand Māori people Category:New Zealand activists
